Description: A Linux File Monitoring Tool.


Installation: 
sudo apt install iWatch
#May vary per linux model 

Note: Their are a variety of commands and styles. We will be covering it as a System Background Process.

1. Depends on iWatch version, you may need to edit the config.
sudo nano /etc/iwatch/iwatch.xml

2. Start System Process.
sudo systemctl start iwatch

3. Enable.
sudo systemctl enable iwatch

4. Verify Status.
systemctl status iwatch

5. View Logs.
sudo journalctl -u iwatch -F


This is the easiest way to ensure it is covering your entire system, that is allowed by the IOT manufacturer.
